The paper proposes a novel algorithm for informative path planning using reinforcement learning for mobile robots with sensing and navigation capabilities. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) due to the use of RL. The algorithm also involves a constrained exploration and exploitation strategy, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses real-world measurement data, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
